<br>
WORLD NOTES:<br>
<br>
Capital Cities:<br>
<br>
Adventurers wandering the streets of the major cities will notice that the locals have taken the time to name certain areas and buildings.<br>
<br>
<br>
Crafting and Tradeskills:<br>
<br>
Secondary tradeskill areas have been built in Camelot, Jordheim and Tir na Nog as well as merchants.<br>
<br>
Camelot: A forge was built near the original lathe near Brach Leof and a lathe was placed near the forge near the castle. Several merchants have moved into the surrounding area as well.<br>
<br>
Jordheim: A forge was built by the lathe near the Temple of the Jotuns and merchants have set up shop in the area to accompany them. A new lathe was constructed near Smith Kiarr.<br>
<br>
Tir na Nog: A forge and lathe were built by the stables near the entrance of the city facing Mag Mell. Merchants have moved into the building opposite the area to assist crafters as well.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Albion World:<br>
<br>
Fishermen in Llyn Barfog have reported that the Legendary Afanc has developed new powers but they seem to be exhibited only under certain conditions.<br>
<br>
Adventurers returning from Hadrian's Wall have reported that ancient hatreds have been rekindled between the Coventina and the Pict nation.<br>
<br>
Midgard World:<br>
<br>
Vanern Swamp: Hagbui have taken residence in several new camps. It would be wise to be wary, as they will attack any who tread on the land they guard.<br>
<br>
<br>
Quests:<br>
<br>
Some of the local barkeeps, filidhs and criers will now give you travel directions to certain dungeons. If you are not within the target level range for any dungeon, you will be told that they have nothing for you at this time.<br>
<br>
Hibernia Quests:<br>
<br>
<br>
A low-level coin and experience quest has been added to Hibernia. Players should talk to their local filidh for more information.<br>
<br>
Midgard Quests:<br>
<br>
Three new quests have been added for levels 1 to 4. These quests give an experience and coin reward only. Speak to your local barkeep for details.<br>
Thorgil, a farmer, has had problems with the tomte on his farm outside of Audliten. He is now sharing a house with Gorne in Audliten and could use help with his tomte problem. Speak to him for more information.<br>
<br>
Albion Quests:<br>
<br>
Three new quests added:-<br>
1) Vadri Pade at the magic shop in Camelot is spreading tales of druids.<br>
<br>
2) Omis of Swanton Keep has news regarding a wizard's rambling of druid uprisings.<br>
<br>
3) It is rumored that Librarian Pelan at The Academy has stumbled upon news of a great and powerful staff!<br>
<br>
Fixes<br>
<br>
Kindred of the Fallen<br>
Increased the &quot;use&quot; radius between the standing stones on step 9.<br>
<br>
Symbol of the Broken<br>
Steps 19-24 were labled incorrectly. They were labled 24-29. This has now been corrected.<br>
<br>
Symbol of the Broken<br>
It was reported that Cirfans was rarely seen. His spawn rate has been modified slightly and should be easier to locate now.<br>
